    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "VAD hemolysis CFD sensitivity analysis",
    "description": "One-at-a-time and variance-based (Sobol) sensitivity analyses were performed varying blood viscosity (±15%), red blood cell mechanical threshold stress (±20%), turbulent dissipation model coefficient (±10%), and inlet flow rate across the five COU operating points. The hemolysis index showed greatest sensitivity to the RBC stress threshold parameter (Sobol total-order index 0.61), moderate sensitivity to viscosity (0.22), and low sensitivity to turbulence coefficient and flow rate perturbations within the operating envelope, confirming that RBC constitutive model calibration is the dominant epistemic driver and that the Monte Carlo UQ budget was correctly allocated."
  },
